==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Truism
<hw>Tru"ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>True</er>.]</ety> <def>An undoubted or self-evident truth; a
statement which is pliantly true; a proposition needing no proof or
argument; -- opposed to <xex>falsism</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Trifling <qex>truisms</qex> clothed in great, swelling words.</q>
<rj><qau>J. P. Smith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Truismatic</ent>⟦br⟧
